## @nuance・23  SN23 NicheImage - OTF Weight Request Form Submitted!

We've filled the OTF Weight Request Form and included some exciting updates on what we are working on!

## Summary

NicheImage is making AI accesible to the masses by effectively commoditizing inference of the best models for different use cases.

By letting miners compete through volume and speed of generation, the subnet becomes fast and able to support vast amounts of requests, useful for live inference in apps as well as dataset creation.

We also share insights on the super-ensemble, the next phase of our subnet will enter planned for July, where we will have categories incentivizing miners to specialize, and together form an ensemble that is better than any single general model. More to come on this.

### Links:

There is a fixed percentage of emission to each model, so if lets say 5 people run a model, they will each get about one fifth of the emission, but if a sixth person join, the incentive will now be divided by six. That is what incentivizes people to use underrepresented models.

### @nuance・23 - NicheImage Adding JugernautX and DreamShaperXL

We have now added JuggernautX and DreamShaperXL, however they will not get incentive until all validators automatically update it at Thursday, May 2, 2024 9:00:00 AM.

This is so that validators have 45 hours to update, and will not be penalized for updating early.

Also, at the same time as the incentive changes we will increase the importance of volume from 20% to 40%. This is so to incentivze higher volumes from miners, on the expense of speed becoming slightly less important.

To make sure the models work as intended, after 24 hours we will move 1% emission to them, from RV and DS. This small change should not affect vtrust noticably.

### Validators

If you are running auto-updates the update will be added automatically. Otherwise run this sometime in the next 45 hours:

```
git pull
pip install -e .
pip uninstall uvloop -y
pm2 restart validator_nicheimage
```

Vtrust will not be affected by this update, but instead at Thursday, May 2, 2024 9:00:00 AM all updated validators will automatically redistribute emission from the RV and DS to JX and dsXL. Failing to be updated in the 45 hours will lead to your validator not having this update, meaning the vtrust would decresase if you dont update in these 45 hours.

### Miners
On Thursday, May 2, 2024 9:00:00 AM we will freeze registration for 30 hours, so that RV and DS miners have time to change their models without being deregistered.

Also, a friendly reminder for the new instructions for starting miners:
```git clone https://github.com/NicheTensor/NicheImage
cd NicheImage
python -m venv main_env
source main_env/bin/activate
pip install -e .
pip uninstall uvloop -y
git submodule update --init --recursive
. generation_models/custom_pipelines/scripts/download_antelopev2.sh```

Updating guide for RV & DreamShaper Miners
### Guide for existing DreamShaper and RealisticVision miners

0. Pull the latest code:

```python
git pull
python -m venv main_env
source main_env/bin/activate
pip install -e .
pip uninstall uvloop -y
git submodule update --init --recursive
. generation_models/custom_pipelines/scripts/download_antelopev2.sh
```

1. Stop mining and endpoint process: `pm2 delete all`
2. Start JuggernautXL or DreamShaperXL Endpoint

```python
source main_env/bin/activate
pm2 start python --name "miner_endpoint" -- -m services.miner_endpoint.app \
--model_name <selected-model-name> \ # JuggernautXL or DreamShaperXL
--num_replicas X --num_gpus Y \ # num_gpus * num_replicas = your_total_gpus_count
```

1. Wait for downloading new model checkpoint, until the server is showed up then start mining process

```python
pm2 start python --name "miner" \
-- \
-m neurons.miner.miner \
--netuid 23 \
--wallet.name <wallet_name> --wallet.hotkey <wallet_hotkey> \
--subtensor.network <network> \ # default is finney
--axon.port <your_public_port> \
--miner.total_volume <your-generation-volume> # default is 40. Change based on your model timeout value and GPU capacity
--miner.max_concurrent_requests <your-max-concurrent-requests> # default is 4. Change based on your model timeout value and GPU capacity
```
